WEBVTT

00:02.035 --> 00:04.800
All right, there's a fridge
full of Steak-Ums,

00:04.871 --> 00:06.533
but you gotta
microwave them.

00:06.606 --> 00:08.131
I don't want you using the stove
when we're gone.

00:08.208 --> 00:09.608
You can't microwave
Steak-Ums.

00:09.676 --> 00:10.609
They get all hard!

00:10.677 --> 00:13.044
If it's a choice
between this and the speed suit,

00:13.113 --> 00:14.911
I choose the speed suit.

00:14.981 --> 00:17.883
Let me see
my junior scientist!

00:17.951 --> 00:19.977
Ahh, I wore that suit

00:20.053 --> 00:21.749
when I had
my first New York assignment.

00:21.821 --> 00:23.312
Ooh, if that suit could talk --

00:23.390 --> 00:26.087
It would say "Kill me!
I'm a hideous monster!"

00:26.159 --> 00:26.990
See?

00:27.060 --> 00:29.393
Your brother is
just jealous.

00:29.462 --> 00:31.294
Oh, yeah, I'm jealous that
I don't get to go to New York

00:31.364 --> 00:33.993
dressed as the Jamaican flag
to work for no pay.

00:34.067 --> 00:35.592
It's an internship,
Hank.

00:35.668 --> 00:38.035
They pay you with experience
and an impressive résumé!

00:38.104 --> 00:41.006
Yeah, I'm gonna load up
the X-1, Doc.

00:41.074 --> 00:42.542
Hey, soldier,
you flying with us?

00:42.609 --> 00:43.599
Oh, no!

00:43.676 --> 00:44.905
He's staying right here,

00:44.978 --> 00:46.913
and he's getting a job
by the time we get back.

00:46.980 --> 00:48.949
I told you that's
gonna be no problem.

00:49.015 --> 00:50.643
But I warn you that,
unlike Dean,

00:50.717 --> 00:52.652
I will not be
working for the man,

00:52.719 --> 00:54.984
<i>and</i> I plan on getting
paid.

00:55.055 --> 00:58.253
Now, I've narrowed down
my list.

00:58.324 --> 01:01.522
Well, at least
you crossed out mafia don,

01:01.594 --> 01:03.392
fire eater,
traveling racecar salesman,

01:03.463 --> 01:05.762
and my favorite --
gigolo.

01:05.832 --> 01:06.822
Once I found out

01:06.900 --> 01:08.835
it had nothing to do
with Italian ice cream,

01:08.902 --> 01:09.767
it lost its allure.

01:09.836 --> 01:10.929
'Sup, Team Venture.

01:11.004 --> 01:13.371
Great! Dermott's gonna
help you get a job.

01:13.440 --> 01:15.409
Uh, Mr. V., I have
a full-time job,

01:15.475 --> 01:18.309
and I teach Ninjitsu classes
on the weekends.

01:18.378 --> 01:21.075
Technically, he wears that
weird, padded giant baby suit

01:21.147 --> 01:23.116
for a rape-prevention
class.

01:23.183 --> 01:24.879
That's a huge
confidence builder.

01:24.951 --> 01:26.385
All right,
we got to get going.

01:26.453 --> 01:28.888
I don't want to have to fly
at night in the X-1.

01:28.955 --> 01:31.083
I get the lights mixed up
with the lasers,

01:31.157 --> 01:33.092
and then I end up
blowing stuff up.

01:33.159 --> 01:35.424
I-I-I just don't
want to blow stuff up

01:35.495 --> 01:36.394
'cause I can't see.

01:36.463 --> 01:38.364
Hank, I get back
in three days.

01:38.431 --> 01:40.400
Four if Hatred got
"The Music Man" tickets.

01:40.467 --> 01:42.629
Ohh...yeah, we got tickets!

01:42.702 --> 01:44.534
♪ We got tickets
to a Broadway show ♪

01:44.604 --> 01:46.402
♪ and that rhymes
with "T"... ♪

01:46.473 --> 01:47.964
I'm gonna go get the X-1.

01:48.041 --> 01:51.341
Four days, Hank,
and you better be employed.

01:56.850 --> 01:59.081
[elevator music plays ]

01:59.152 --> 02:01.747
Yeah, uh,
what is a pop-top?

02:01.821 --> 02:03.813
Uh, we take a toaster tart,

02:03.890 --> 02:05.825
we shave off the top,
and that's served on a bed

02:05.892 --> 02:08.225
of kind of
crumbled toaster tart.

02:08.294 --> 02:10.422
Okay.
I'll have that and a --

02:10.497 --> 02:12.125
Fruit punch.
It's all we got.

02:12.198 --> 02:13.928
All righty.
You have cherry?

02:14.000 --> 02:14.831
Well, maybe.

02:14.901 --> 02:16.233
Maybe? What is maybe?

02:16.302 --> 02:19.295
Maybe is we have red.

02:19.372 --> 02:22.137
Not quite what I had in mind
for employment.

02:22.208 --> 02:24.040
I see you have an interest

02:24.110 --> 02:25.772
in our fine collection
of remote controls.

02:25.845 --> 02:27.871
Well, if you put your address
on our mailing list,

02:27.947 --> 02:29.313
we'll be sure to contact you
when we get more in.

02:29.382 --> 02:31.146
Hank, you know
my address.

02:31.217 --> 02:32.310
It's here.
I live here.

02:32.385 --> 02:34.980
And I don't plan on buying back
any more of my remotes.

02:35.054 --> 02:36.522
But I am coming back
for my shoes.

02:36.589 --> 02:38.080
I hope we carry
your size.

02:38.158 --> 02:41.026
Hank, you carry my size because
those are all my shoes.

02:41.094 --> 02:41.993
[ bell dings ]

02:42.061 --> 02:44.428
I'm sorry.
I have another customer.

02:44.497 --> 02:45.487
Banking needs?

02:45.565 --> 02:49.434
Uh, no, I-I just need
a few things notarized.

02:49.502 --> 02:51.232
That's two departments
down.

02:51.304 --> 02:53.364
Dermott, finish up
with this gentleman.

02:53.439 --> 02:56.204
All right, these are all
final-sale items.

02:58.178 --> 03:00.443
Changing the terms
of my child support.

03:00.513 --> 03:03.449
Remember when your wife used
to screw you without paperwork?

03:03.516 --> 03:06.008
That's very appropriate
for the boy to hear.

03:06.085 --> 03:08.111
You hear a lot
in my line of work.

03:08.188 --> 03:10.748
Okay, just sign here,
initial here, and here.

03:10.823 --> 03:12.815
Nikki, don't be a douche.
Just come pick me up!

03:12.892 --> 03:13.882
Dude, what?!

03:13.960 --> 03:15.792
Do you carry
double-A batteries?

03:15.862 --> 03:17.797
Hank removed all the batteries
from my remotes.

03:17.864 --> 03:19.696
I don't know.
Try the electronics department.

03:19.766 --> 03:21.894
Mom was supposed to pick me up
two hours ago!

03:21.968 --> 03:22.958
You gotta!

03:23.036 --> 03:24.800
And I assume you're
the third party?

03:24.871 --> 03:27.636
Compared to Mr. Fun,
I'm the entire party.

03:27.707 --> 03:29.767
Dude, my mom's freakin'
AWOL.

03:29.842 --> 03:30.866
I need a ride home.

03:30.944 --> 03:32.879
So, your mom's missing?

03:32.946 --> 03:35.506
Okay, meet me at that table
over there.

03:35.582 --> 03:37.312
One moment, gentlemen.

03:37.383 --> 03:42.048
Mine, mine,
mine, mine...

03:48.228 --> 03:49.252
Tssss!

03:49.329 --> 03:50.160
Smooth.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.163
[ coughs ]

03:51.231 --> 03:52.164
Buy you a drink?

03:52.232 --> 03:55.134
Are you seri--
totally!

03:55.201 --> 03:56.362
What is this, apple juice?

03:56.436 --> 03:57.563
Only the best.

03:57.637 --> 03:58.969
So, what's the score?

03:59.038 --> 03:59.903
Badger game?

03:59.973 --> 04:02.306
Blow some cabbage
on a dirty bang-tail?

04:02.375 --> 04:04.503
Get dizzy
on some Jasper's dame?

04:04.577 --> 04:07.240
Dude, I can't find my mom,
so I need a ride home.

04:07.313 --> 04:10.010
Missing person?

04:10.083 --> 04:11.415
Okay, I'll take the case.

04:11.484 --> 04:13.180
Now let's start
rom the beginning.

04:13.253 --> 04:15.347
Tell me everything.

04:15.421 --> 04:18.185
[thinking ]
It started out as
another case of "where's mommy?"

04:18.257 --> 04:20.887
then it turned tail faster
than a kicked pooch.

04:20.959 --> 04:23.259
Either I'm being played
for a patsy

04:23.329 --> 04:26.561
or that palooka is
actually Brock's kid.

04:26.633 --> 04:28.625
[ knock on door]

04:28.701 --> 04:29.896
You gonna come in,

04:29.969 --> 04:30.959
or are you looking
for studs in the wall?

04:31.037 --> 04:32.972
If I thought there were
studs here,

04:33.039 --> 04:34.166
I wouldn't be
sitting outside

04:34.240 --> 04:35.606
trying to get a snack
from Café Hank.

04:35.675 --> 04:36.836
Café's closed.

04:36.909 --> 04:39.777
But if you just want to wag
your chin, grab some bench.

04:39.846 --> 04:40.939
Ahh!

04:41.014 --> 04:42.482
When I moved in with Orpheus,

04:42.548 --> 04:43.982
he neglected to tell me

04:44.050 --> 04:46.610
that there's nothing around here
open past 8:30.

04:46.686 --> 04:50.282
Ahh, the old
private-dick game huh?

04:50.356 --> 04:53.849
I'm more public and less private
about the dick game these days,

04:53.926 --> 04:56.293
but because I'm bored out
of my gourd,

04:56.362 --> 04:57.227
let's hear the case.

04:57.297 --> 04:58.526
Well, Dermott--

04:58.598 --> 05:00.328
The big creepy kid you hang
around with?

05:00.400 --> 05:01.333
The same.

05:01.401 --> 05:02.767
Well, he can't find his mom.

05:02.835 --> 05:03.768
Solved!

05:03.836 --> 05:05.202
She picked him up
four hours ago.

05:05.271 --> 05:06.102
You were right there.

05:06.172 --> 05:07.265
Yeah, that was solved.

05:07.340 --> 05:09.673
But when he was giving me
the facts of the case,

05:09.742 --> 05:11.210
he dropped a bombshell
right on my lap.

05:11.277 --> 05:13.212
I found out something
I can't believe.

05:13.279 --> 05:14.838
I -- I don't want to believe it.

05:14.914 --> 05:16.906
Did he tell you he likes
to kill small animals?

05:16.983 --> 05:18.952
Because that kid's wa-eird!

05:19.018 --> 05:21.214
Right? I used to think that,
too, but, no.

05:21.287 --> 05:23.847
He comes out and tells me
he thinks his dad is Brock.

05:23.923 --> 05:25.789
Get out! Really?

05:25.858 --> 05:28.054
Seriously.
And I don't know what to do.

05:28.127 --> 05:30.028
Well, you have to solve
this case!

05:30.096 --> 05:31.394
That's what the sign is for!

05:31.464 --> 05:32.762
That's why you have the hat!

05:32.832 --> 05:34.460
That's why you have the whip!

05:34.534 --> 05:35.365
Wait. Why do you have a whip?

05:35.435 --> 05:36.562
Came with the hat.

05:36.636 --> 05:37.660
It's a detective's whip.

05:37.737 --> 05:38.727
[ knock on door]

05:38.805 --> 05:39.670
In the back!

05:44.477 --> 05:46.036
Hey, has anyone seen Dermott?

05:46.112 --> 05:48.377
He left with your mom
like four hours ago.

05:48.448 --> 05:50.383
I drove all the way
from the Highlands.

05:50.450 --> 05:52.510
You think he could've called me
to tell me he got a ride.

05:52.585 --> 05:53.609
You know Dermott.

05:53.686 --> 05:55.655
He's not one for politeness,
but he's a good kid.

05:55.722 --> 05:56.781
If you don't get an apology,

05:56.856 --> 05:58.381
I'll make him
buy you flowers, deal?

05:58.458 --> 06:00.154
Deal.
What are you guys doing?

06:00.226 --> 06:01.524
Me and Al have a job.

06:01.594 --> 06:03.586
I'd bend your ear on it,
but a pretty dame like you

06:03.663 --> 06:05.029
shouldn't get involved
with this kind of thing.

06:05.098 --> 06:06.031
It's too dangerous.

06:06.099 --> 06:08.091
Dangerous?
Uh-huh.

06:08.167 --> 06:09.567
No, seriously,
what are you guys doing?

06:09.635 --> 06:10.864
Scram, doll!

06:10.937 --> 06:12.769
I don't want to think about
a body like yours

06:12.839 --> 06:13.829
getting busted up
over this.

06:13.906 --> 06:15.465
[ chuckles ]
Okay.

06:15.541 --> 06:16.531
Thanks.

06:16.609 --> 06:19.272
Uh, hey, Hank,
I just want to thank you

06:19.345 --> 06:21.576
for keeping Dermott
out of trouble and stuff.

06:21.647 --> 06:23.013
Like I said,
he's a good kid.

06:23.082 --> 06:23.981
Now drift, doll.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.382
We got to get some work done.

06:25.451 --> 06:27.010
Okay.
Bye, Hank.

06:27.086 --> 06:28.645
And, um...
- Al.

06:28.721 --> 06:31.088
I'm his, uh, gal Friday,
I guess.

06:31.157 --> 06:32.489
Right, right...

06:32.558 --> 06:35.153
Oh, Hank, um, I don't think
Dermott's going to apologize

06:35.228 --> 06:39.598
to anyone, so, uh, why don't <i>you</i>
stop by with those flowers?

06:39.665 --> 06:41.327
Hank, you were amazing!

06:41.401 --> 06:42.767
When did you get so smooth?

06:42.835 --> 06:43.700
It's the hat!

06:43.770 --> 06:46.137
I have had a crush on Dermott's
sister forever!

06:46.205 --> 06:48.265
I've never said anything
to her before!

06:48.341 --> 06:50.537
She was on you like
Sid on Nancy!

06:50.610 --> 06:52.306
All right, Hank, I'm in.

06:52.378 --> 06:55.712
I'll be your partner
'til we solve this case

06:55.782 --> 06:58.752
or till I get
completely bored doing it!

07:00.853 --> 07:03.288
HANK:
Me and Al hit the dives
and flophouses

07:03.356 --> 07:05.882
trying to dig up
some info on this dame.

07:05.958 --> 07:08.621
We had the kind of luck that
turns a professional gambler

07:08.694 --> 07:10.526
into an amateur murderer.

07:10.596 --> 07:12.929
Your basic boob ain't
too keen on dicks.

07:12.999 --> 07:14.262
When a bum sees a dick coming,

07:14.333 --> 07:16.996
he don't stick around
for the credits.

07:17.069 --> 07:20.335
Seems this old broad wasn't so
popular with the men folk.

07:20.406 --> 07:23.137
Every jobbie in this burg knew
the old frail,

07:23.209 --> 07:26.941
but nobody copped
to pitching woo.

07:27.013 --> 07:28.481
Geez, can you blame
them?

07:28.548 --> 07:29.914
Look at this old townie.

07:29.982 --> 07:33.510
Hank, what was that about the
bums not liking dicks coming?

07:33.586 --> 07:34.485
Ow!

07:34.554 --> 07:36.113
What!
He-- he said that!

07:36.189 --> 07:38.181
Or was it boobs --
Ow!

07:38.257 --> 07:40.089
Sorry, Hank.
Never met her before.

07:40.159 --> 07:41.923
She said I knocked her up?
- Her kid said you did.

07:41.994 --> 07:43.622
What, are you friends
with babies now?

07:43.696 --> 07:44.891
The baby's grown up.

07:44.964 --> 07:46.091
This happened 17 years ago.

07:46.165 --> 07:48.066
Oh, I thought now that
you're hanging around

07:48.134 --> 07:50.262
with guys like this --
- What are you staring at?

07:50.336 --> 07:53.170
I -- I'm sorry.
Have we slept together before?

07:53.239 --> 07:55.105
- Um, no.
- Would you like to?

07:55.174 --> 07:56.437
Al, quit eyeballing
the Nance.

07:56.509 --> 07:57.340
We're on a case.

07:57.410 --> 07:59.504
Yeah, I think
I'd remember this one.

07:59.579 --> 08:00.979
I don't even want to think about

08:01.047 --> 08:02.743
what this mess looked
like back then.

08:02.815 --> 08:03.748
Could not have been good.

08:03.816 --> 08:05.341
Maybe on a lonely
night...

08:05.418 --> 08:07.148
I've never been
that drunk,

08:07.220 --> 08:08.449
and I've never been
that desperate.

08:08.521 --> 08:10.149
Sorry, kid.

08:10.223 --> 08:11.282
[ horn honks ]

08:11.357 --> 08:13.349
[ ominous music plays ]

08:20.366 --> 08:22.358
[ footsteps approaching ]

08:24.000 --> 08:30.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

09:05.478 --> 09:06.343
Relax!

09:06.412 --> 09:08.074
I just want to talk to you.

09:08.147 --> 09:09.638
I -- I didn't steal
those games!

09:09.715 --> 09:12.184
They were defective so they're
just being thrown out!

09:12.251 --> 09:13.742
I'm not mall security!

09:13.819 --> 09:14.752
What -- so who are you?

09:14.820 --> 09:16.755
[whip cracks ]
He works with me.

09:16.822 --> 09:19.189
He's The Alchemist,
seeker of truth.

09:19.258 --> 09:21.625
You're a superhero guy and
you're hanging out with Hank?

09:21.694 --> 09:24.528
Look, Pudgy McTalk-a-lot,
I just got dumped by my lover

09:24.597 --> 09:27.863
who then tossed me out
on my jobless ass

09:27.934 --> 09:30.062
so I had to move in
with my boring team member

09:30.136 --> 09:33.334
who lives in the 'burbs
and never does squat!

09:33.406 --> 09:35.875
And I just -- I just told you
too much, didn't I!

09:35.942 --> 09:37.535
Uh, dude, no shit.

09:37.610 --> 09:39.511
Geez, Al,
let the palooka down.

09:39.579 --> 09:41.775
We have a couple more questions
about your case.

09:41.847 --> 09:44.009
Case?
I needed a ride home, doofus.

09:44.083 --> 09:47.076
What is this, "the case of my
mom forgot her cellphone"?

09:47.153 --> 09:48.177
No, Wisenheimer!

09:48.254 --> 09:50.189
It's the case of "you tell us
the truth

09:50.256 --> 09:51.884
or Al will make your
dentist a rich man"!

09:51.958 --> 09:52.982
What are you --

09:53.059 --> 09:53.992
Oh, right! Sorry.

09:54.060 --> 09:56.962
You tell me your old man
is Brock Samson.

09:57.029 --> 09:59.260
You think I'm gonna
let that slide? Huh?!

09:59.332 --> 10:01.324
I did some checking, and your
facts ain't adding up.

10:01.400 --> 10:02.527
Samson's a ringer.

10:02.602 --> 10:04.332
Well, that's what my freakin'
mom told me, you douche.

10:04.403 --> 10:07.134
Now let me go.
I got to get back to work.

10:07.206 --> 10:09.072
Come on, Hank.
He's a kid.

10:09.141 --> 10:10.200
Don't make me hit a kid.

10:10.276 --> 10:11.835
Oh, yeah, like
I'd even feel it.

10:11.911 --> 10:14.005
You're like Danny Devito's
penguin.

10:14.080 --> 10:16.743
[ coughing ]

10:16.816 --> 10:19.217
Hey, man, my God!
Take it down!

10:19.285 --> 10:20.275
Ugh.

10:20.353 --> 10:22.015
My mom gave me this,
all right?

10:22.088 --> 10:23.579
She said it was my dad's.

10:23.656 --> 10:25.591
Okay?
I'm telling you the truth.

10:25.658 --> 10:27.524
Now I got to get back to work
before I get fired.

10:27.593 --> 10:28.993
[sniffles ]
I'm not crying.

10:29.061 --> 10:30.324
He's telling the truth.

10:30.396 --> 10:31.887
Al, go get the boiler.

10:31.964 --> 10:34.729
No clue.
Car? Is that the car?

10:34.800 --> 10:35.859
Yeah, the car.

10:35.935 --> 10:37.836
[wheezing ]

10:37.903 --> 10:40.805
I am <i>way</i> sorry for making
a grown-up punch you, man.

10:40.873 --> 10:42.273
What?
That's cool.

10:42.341 --> 10:44.003
You know, I actually stole
those video games,

10:44.076 --> 10:45.135
so I had it coming.

10:52.418 --> 10:53.477
Hey, boss.

10:53.552 --> 10:54.781
What can I get you?

10:54.854 --> 10:57.016
I see you made some
changes to my joint.

10:57.089 --> 10:59.854
I got to tell you, it's
always been my secret dream

10:59.925 --> 11:01.325
to run a hash house.

11:01.394 --> 11:03.056
I am just loving this!

11:03.129 --> 11:05.462
Oh, and I made some adjustments
to the menu.

11:05.531 --> 11:08.592
So, basically, we, uh, just
serve eggs now.

11:08.668 --> 11:10.193
Mostly scrambled.

11:10.269 --> 11:11.464
And all with ketchup.

11:11.537 --> 11:13.301
So, what can I get you?

11:13.372 --> 11:15.364
- Cup of java?
- Two.

11:15.441 --> 11:17.808
Gotcha.
Two coffees coming up!

11:17.877 --> 11:18.867
Psst!

11:18.944 --> 11:19.912
Hank.

11:19.979 --> 11:21.811
Psst! Hank.
Hank.

11:21.881 --> 11:24.316
Heard you're working
the Fictel case.

11:24.383 --> 11:26.375
Yeah, Dermott Fictel.
He misses his old man.

11:26.452 --> 11:28.648
Fingered Samson, but it's
starting to get rotten.

11:28.721 --> 11:30.713
So you've met Nikki?
Nikki Fictel?

11:30.790 --> 11:31.655
And how.

11:31.724 --> 11:33.283
Yeah, she's a looker,
that one.

